Fisher-Price is recalling 83 toys due to lead paint, impacting Mattel's income by $30 million.
Concerns arise over Chinese-made products, with 80% of toys originating from China.
Mattel's strict safety standards are questioned as recalls increase.
Parents worry about tainted toys and potential health risks.
Thomas the Tank Engine fans face expensive recalls, highlighting the dominance of Chinese products in the US market.
Consumer advocates demand stricter regulations on toy safety.
RC2 initiates a recall for Thomas & Friends toys, implementing lead testing and safety measures in China.
Mattel and other companies face scrutiny over product safety and oversight.
